    "exportedAt": "2026-06-23T00:00:00.000Z",
    "note": "v2 (2026-06-23): fixed insights 6 (QR scans by outcome) and 17 (Copy-format vs Clean exports) — both were multi-aggregation `timeseries` line charts, a shape the imported-insight renderer plots as a single series (so they showed only one outcome/extension, or read empty); both are now `groupBy` over the distinguishing dimension(s) (`type`+`reason` and `type`), the same shape every working multi-line chart here uses. No taxonomy change. The 1.1 surface board — 'did the new bets land?' One board per beat (engine-depth E1/E2, App Intents S1, QR, V3 privacy-card growth loop, ai-A advisor, Copy-as-you-want formats). All events ship in 1.1.0; insights read empty until 1.1 reaches users. SLICE BY `tier` for the Pro-vs-free behavioral read on any of these (every signal carries `tier` + `surface` defaults). Companion boards: Dashboard-LinkClean-Core-Usage.json (durable loop health, all surfaces folded in) and Dashboard-LinkClean-Monetization.json (the IAP funnel — `advisorAccept` + `formatPicker` are the two NEW 1.1 paywall gates that read THERE). KEY THRESHOLDS: unwrap rate ≥ 5% means E1 is paying for itself (else most users hand us clean links); App Intents share ≥ 10% of weekly exports means the OS-surface bet landed; QR scan→action ≥ 60% means scans yield exports (lower = scan-and-bounce, signals the result sheet is the leak); Stats.Card share rate ≥ 10% per populated view means V3 is functioning as the viral loop the roadmap predicted; advisor accept rate ≥ 30% (any tier) means it earns its sheet space; preset-vs-custom inverting (custom > preset) is the strongest signal that Pro customization will sell. OPEN QUESTIONS: (a) the heuristic tier suggests on every device but the model tier only on Apple-Intelligence hardware — split insight 14/15 by hardware availability isn't possible here (no signal); look for tier-share drift over time as iOS 26+ Apple-Intelligence adoption grows. (b) Control Center and the widget both report `intentSurface=clipboard` — if the share of clipboard intents stays high without the corresponding Settings.QRButton/widget-add behavior, we may be over-fitting one surface (defer the split until shape demands it; analytics.md §IntentSurface).",
    "dynamicFields": [
      {
        "type": "event",
        "name": "Home.URL.cleaned",
        "hint": "App-process clean. The denominator for insight 1 (unwrap rate) carries `unwrapped`."
      },
      {
